<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEGALIZING DRUGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Your article, "Colombian Cocaine Prosecutor Calls Worldwide Drug War Futile" 
is the most sensible policy I've read in a long time (July 18). 
</P>
<P>
 The demand for drugs fuels the market! It is the source of our prisons being 
overloaded.The money alone to build more prisons could be used for improving 
education. 
</P>
<P>
 As stated in the article, "like Prohibition the drug war has created massive 
police corruption, an exploding prison population and a rise in street violence 
with no noticeable drop in drug use." 
</P>
<P>
 "Narco-trafficking is a big business and business stops being good business 
when it stops profiting," Gustavo de Greif, Colombian cocaine prosecutor 
remarked.  
</P>
<P>
 The United States should abandon the current drug policy. 
</P>
<P>
 JACK GILMAN MD 
</P>
<P>
 West Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
