<TEXT>
<P>
 Big Sisters of Los Angeles needs volunteers to mentor young girls who are 
believed to be at risk for dropping out of school, getting pregnant, joining 
gangs or taking drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, established in 1982, pairs women and girls according to common 
interests for up to four hours of activities per week. 
</P>
<P>
 Big Sisters can provide the friendship and guidance often missing in the lives 
of the girls, said spokeswoman Susan Pasternak. 
