<P>
TOPICS / BRIEFLY; ENVIRONMENT: TOXIC WASTE REMOVAL PROGRAM RESUMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Los Angeles continues its hazardous waste removal program this 
week with collection points in the Fairfax and Hancock Park districts. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents must make an appointment with the Hazmobile Program, which will be 
collecting toxic household wastes Aug. 4-6 and Aug. 11-13. 
</P>
<P>
 The Public Works Department will disclose the location of the collection 
points only to those who make an appointment. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hazmobile Program, in place since February, gathers waste such as motor 
oil, pesticides, cleaners, paint and other household chemicals for safe and 
legal disposal. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents may drive through the collection line from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. once 
they have made their appointment. 
</P>
<P>
 For appointments call (800) 98-TOXIC from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
