<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HOLLYWOOD; MAN CHARGED WITH BREAK-IN AT SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Criminal charges were filed Tuesday against a man accused of breaking into the 
Hollywood High School library over the weekend and causing more than $1,000 in 
damage. 
</P>
<P>
 Jerry Douglas Jensen, 32, who lists Torrance as his hometown but is believed 
to be a transient in the Hollywood area, was charged with trespassing and 
vandalism in a complaint filed in Hollywood Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 The trespassing charge could result in a six-month jail term and $1,000 fine, 
said Deputy City Atty. Bill Sterling. The vandalism charge carries a special 
allegation that the damage caused was between $1,000 and $5,000, which enhances 
the maximum penalty to one year in jail and a $5,000 fine, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Unified School District officials estimated the damage at $1,070. 
</P>
</TEXT>
