<P>
ROLLER HOCKEY; BLADES TAKE CHARGE EARLY, WIN, 8-5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The L.A. Blades, whose habit has been to give up early leads and fight back, 
got their defense in gear early in an 8-5 victory over the Anaheim Bullfrogs 
Wednesday at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blades held off the Bullfrogs for 21 seconds of a 4-on-2 power play early 
in the first quarter, and the momentum of that defensive stand led to goals 11 
seconds apart from Mike Callahan and Brett Kurtz for a 2-0 lead that later 
became 5-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Blade goalie Max Mikhailovsky, pulled against Las Vegas when ineffective a 
week ago, made 46 saves. Averaging 33.9 saves a game, he had 25 by halftime in 
front of 4,891. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory puts the first-place Blades (15-4) two games ahead of second-place 
Anaheim (12-5) in the Roller Hockey International Pacific Division. MATT WHITE 
</P>
