<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; FREE VAN SERVICE OFFERED TO VETERANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beginning today, Simi Valley veterans can ride for free to their medical 
appointments in Los Angeles in a new van. 
</P>
<P>
 The 14-seat van was purchased after members of the Simi Valley chapter of 
Disabled American Veterans persuaded the city of Simi Valley and the National 
Disabled American Veterans Department to donate $18,000 to buy the van. 
</P>
<P>
 The free van service is available to veterans living in Simi Valley. The van 
will arrive at 8 a.m. each weekday at the Simi Valley Senior Citizens Center at 
3900 Avenida Simi, take passengers to the Veterans Medical Center in North 
Hills and then drive them home. 
</P>
<P>
 Veterans interested in arranging for a ride should call the Senior Center at 
526-9237 at least three days in advance to reserve a space. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
