<TEXT>
<P>
 After weeks of haggling over contract details, the Democratic National 
Committee and Chicago have closed a $32.1-million deal for the city to be the 
site of the party's 1996 presidential nominating convention. 
</P>
<P>
 DNC Chairman David Wilhelm is to make the announcement today in Chicago with 
