time Chicago has been host to a national political convention since 1968, when 
the Democratic gathering was marred by violent protests against the Vietnam 
War. 
</P>
<P>
 Democratic officials had earlier settled on Chicago as their preference but 
have been negotiating with the city over unresolved issues, such as making sure 
enough space was available to house the convention. 
