<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson has appointed Kate Squires, a Riverside County lawyer who ran 
unsuccessfully in the June primary for the Republican nomination to the U.S. 
Senate, to an $88,056-a-year position on the state Workers' Compensation 
Appeals Board. 
</P>
<P>
 Squires, of Corona, heads a legal education and publishing company and has 
experience in corporate law firms. 
</P>
<P>
 As a commissioner on the workers' compensation board, which has quasi-judicial 
powers, Squires will hear appeals and participate in decisions regarding 
benefits for workers who are injured at work. 
