<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; TEACHERS, 
DISTRICT AGREE TO HALT TALKS FOR A WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After meeting for about three hours on Wednesday, negotiators for the Los 
Angeles Unified School District and the teachers union agreed to halt their 
contract talks for a week to give both sides time to explore some of the ideas 
floated during the past two days. 
</P>
<P>
 The contract negotiations, centering on United Teachers-Los Angeles' demand 
for restoring a 10% cut in teacher salaries, are scheduled to resume Aug. 10. 
Board of Education President Mark Slavkin said the board will meet in closed 
session this morning for an update, and he and UTLA spokeswoman Catherine Carey 
said both sides expect to keep their promise not to talk publicly about the 
negotiations until some agreement is reached. 
</P>
</TEXT>
