<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: BELL GARDENS; BICYCLE 
CLUB CASINO'S GENERAL MANAGER QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 George G. Hardie, longtime general manager of the Bicycle Club Casino, 
resigned this week to pursue other interests, including a race for county 
commissioner in Clark County, Nev., which includes Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Hardie, a prominent figure in California's card club industry, said he will 
continue to serve as a consultant to the Bicycle Club, which he has managed 
since 1984. 
</P>
<P>
 The casino is being run on an interim basis by a trustee for the government, 
which seized the club in 1990 after it was found to have been built in part 
with $12 million in laundered drug money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
