<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
ROOMMATE CHARGED IN FATAL SHOOTING OF DEPUTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Los Angeles County sheriff's deputy who was believed to have committed 
suicide was actually a homicide victim, and the slain deputy's roommate has 
been charged with the killing, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Margarita Rodriguez, 40, pleaded not guilty in Municipal Court Tuesday to 
fatally shooting Deputy Lori Anderson, 27, at their Fairfax District apartment 
on July 25. Rodriguez is being held in lieu of $1 million bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez was arrested Friday, said Los Angeles Police Detective Lloyd Parry. 
He said the shooting grew out of a dispute between the women. 
</P>
