<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; GUNMAN WOUNDS 2 MEN IN ALLEYWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were wounded early Wednesday when a gunman opened fire in an alleyway 
for no apparent reason, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The gunman and a companion -- described as white men in their early 20s -- 
fled after the shooting on the 7600 block of Amberleaf Circle. 
</P>
<P>
 Juan Vergara, 22, was reported in critical condition Wednesday at UCI Medical 
Center in Orange after undergoing surgery for a gunshot wound to the stomach. 
Angel Campos Silia, 22, was released Wednesday afternoon from Western Medical 
Center-Santa Ana after being treated for wounds to the thigh. Both victims are 
of Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 A friend of the two men who was at the scene was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims were in the alley shortly after midnight when the two assailants 
approached and one suddenly fired five or six rounds from a small-caliber 
handgun, said Lt. Luis Ochoa. He said the victims apparently did not know the 
attackers. 
</P>
<P>
 "There's absolutely no idea about the reason for the shooting," Ochoa said. 
"As far as a motive, we just don't know right now." 
</P>
<P>
 The gunman was described as being about 5 feet, 7 inches tall with 
close-cropped light hair. He was wearing gray pants and a white T-shirt, Ochoa 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
