his right knee today and be sidelined at least three weeks. Hasty will have 
scar tissue removed that formed after surgery in March. . . . Dolphin 
quarterback Dan Marino and his worrisome right leg are ready to take the next 
step in his comeback from a torn Achilles' tendon with a start in Saturday's 
game against Pittsburgh. But it was surprising to some since Marino still walks 
with a limp and admits that his right ankle hurts. 
