<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY: CORAM HEALTHCARE OF NEWPORT TO MOVE OFFICES TO COLORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coram Healthcare Corp. said Wednesday that it plans to move to Boulder, Colo., 
within a year and build a headquarters there that will be staffed by 60 to 80 
new employees. 
</P>
<P>
 Coram, which specializes in providing intravenous drug remedies to patients at 
their homes, now has only four employees in its Newport Beach headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
 The company was formed earlier this year in a merger among four companies, 
including Ontario-based Curaflex Health Services. About 200 former Curaflex 
employees still work in an office in Ontario; Coram managers aren't sure 
whether those jobs will move to Boulder, said Don Cook, a Coram vice president. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, Coram has announced that it will buy Houston-based HMSS, which 
provides similar home health services. HMSS is now owned by Secomerica Inc., a 
holding company also based in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials would not disclose the sale price. If approved by government 
regulators, the transaction is expected to be completed by mid-September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
