<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CHATSWORTH; OFFICER WOUNDED IN GUNFIGHT RECOVERING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A reserve police officer involved in a gun battle at a Chatsworth nightclub is 
recovering from a wound to the upper leg at a local hospital, where his 
condition has been upgraded, a nursing supervisor said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Wilson, 34, was shot by two teen-agers wearing ski masks as he left the 
Cowboy Palace Saloon late Monday night with a female friend, police 
said.Wilson, a San Fernando Police reserve officer, returned fire, striking 
each of the suspected would-be robbers several times. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities identified the assailants as a 16-year-old Sun Valley resident, 
whose name was withheld, and Mjomo Abdul Anderson, 19, of North Hollywood. The 
youth is in serious condition at Northridge Hospital Medical Center, and 
Anderson is being held at the USC-County Jail Ward, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both were booked for attempted robbery and attempted murder. JEANNETTE 
REGALADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
