<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: LAKE VIEW TERRACE; PAXTON STREET WILL UNDERGO RESURFACING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Traffic on Paxton Street from west of the Foothill Freeway to west of Lopez 
Canyon Road may slow considerably during daytime working hours for two weeks in 
September.  
</P>
<P>
 A project to resurface the existing roadway in an unincorporated area near 
Lake View Terrace will start at the beginning of the month and is expected to 
take 10 working days to complete, according to Los Angeles County Supervisor Ed 
Edelman's office. 
</P>
<P>
 The project will be performed under a $57,258 contract awarded by the county 
to Boral Resources Inc. of Pomona. A portion of the money will be reimbursed by 
the state under a program that administers grants to local agencies for public 
road improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 "These improvements will increase safety, reduce maintenance costs and extend 
the service life of these roads," Edelman said. ANTONIO OLIVO 
