<TEXT>
<P>
 PUC Acts on Cellular Matters: The California Public Utilities Commission said 
it will apply to the Federal Communications Commission to continue its 
regulatory authority over the cellular telephone business. In a victory for 
cellular resellers, who buy circuits in bulk from the major carriers such as 
McCaw Cellular and AirTouch Communications and resell them to customers, the 
commission also ruled that the carriers must now resell bulk circuits with less 
onerous conditions. The resellers said the two related decisions could cut 
cellular rates by up to 30%, but the major carriers say continued regulation of 
the cellular industry will ultimately stifle competition and keep prices 
higher. 
