<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST AREA; CHALLENGER BOWS OUT OF ASSEMBLY RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The only challenger facing Democratic Assemblyman Willard H. Murray Jr. has 
withdrawn from the November race for the 52nd Assembly District, clearing the 
way for the incumbent to serve a fourth term. 
</P>
<P>
 Republican candidate Richard A. Rorex, 57, of Gardena said he withdrew last 
week after being hired as a maintenance mechanic with the U.S. Postal Service 
processing center in Bell. Postal Service attorneys advised Rorex that postal 
workers cannot hold partisan political office. 
</P>
<P>
 Murray was considered a strong favorite, anyway, in the heavily Democratic 
district that includes Gardena, as well as the Southeast communities of 
Compton, Paramount and Lynwood. 
</P>
<P>
 Rorex's name will still appear on the November ballot, county elections 
officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
