<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: CARSON; COUNCIL OKS BONUS FOR WORKERS, BUT NO RAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Although no municipal employees will get a raise this year, the City Council 
has approved a one-time payment of $500 for each city worker. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members excluded themselves from the payment, which is funded from a 
surplus in last year's budget. The payment is in consideration for a 90-day 
extension of employee contracts. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilwoman Lorelie S. Olaes voted against the payment because of the city's 
financial problems and cuts in the 1994-95 budget. 
</P>
<P>
 Rather than spend the money on a onetime payment, she said she would favor 
spending about $147,000 to retain seven part-time workers scheduled to be laid 
off. 
</P>
<P>
 The item passed on a 4-1 vote. MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</TEXT>
