<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HARBOR AREA; 'ONE STOP' BUSINESS PERMIT OFFICE TO OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gayle Wilson, Gov. Pete Wilson's wife, will open the state's first Business 
Revitalization Center satellite office in San Pedro today at 12:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will be a "one-stop shop" to expedite business permits and provide 
information to local businesses, said Councilman Rudy Svorinich Jr., who 
represents the harbor area. 
</P>
<P>
 The center, in Svorinich's harbor district office at 638 S. Beacon St., Suite 
200, initially will be open one day a week, said Barry Glickman, a spokesman 
for Svorinich. 
</P>
