<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HARBOR AREA; HEARING TO FOCUS ON 2 COMMERCIAL PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Community Redevelopment Agency will hold a public hearing 
today on the future of two commercial developments in San Pedro and Wilmington. 
</P>
<P>
 The Beacon Street Redevelopment Project, adopted by the City Council in 1964, 
is a plan to revitalize 60 acres of San Pedro's commercial core. 
</P>
<P>
 In Wilmington, redevelopment efforts since 1974 have transformed an oil field 
into a 232-acre site known as the Wilmington Industrial Park. The area has 70 
businesses employing more than 1,000 workers, said Marc Littman, an agency 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 "The projects are ongoing, but under state legislation that became effective 
in January, public hearings must be held on what the game plan is and how much 
money is going to be spent over the next five years," Littman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The hearing will begin at 9 a.m. in the second-floor boardroom of the Los 
Angeles Harbor Department, 425 S. Palos Verdes St., San Pedro.  
</P>
<P>
 For information or copies of the draft plan: (310) 521-0700. 
</P>
</TEXT>
